{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos700.erdos_700.parts.ii https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos700.erdos_700.parts.ii.","id":"vf_0d65b6d5756cd31a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #700: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let\\[f(n)=\\min_{1<k\\leq n/2}\\textrm{gcd}\\left(n,\\binom{n}{k}\\right).\\]{UL}\n{LI}Characterise those composite $n$ such that $f(n)=n/P(n)$, where $P(n)$ is the largest prime dividing $n$.{/LI}\n{LI}Are there infinitely many composite $n$ such that $f(n)>n^{1/2}$?{/LI}\n{LI} Is it true that, for every composite $n$,\\[f(n) \\ll_A \\frac{n}{(\\log n)^A}\\]for every $A>0$?{/LI}\n{/UL} Current best: This implies\\[f(n) \\leq (1+o(1))\\frac{n}{\\log n}.\\]It is known that $f(n)=n/P(n)$ when $n$ is the product of two primes. Prize: no. OEIS: A091963. Tags: binomial coefficients, number theory.","id":"vf_230a2035cdaecd32","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"OBLIGATION (Erdos #700). BANKED: f(n)=min gcd(n,C(n,k)) recomputed for the cited cases (semiprime and prime-power families). OPEN: characterize f(n) in general beyond the verified families.","id":"vf_2db3437d1512c222","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"#700 RE-ASSESSED after reading erdosproblems comments (Tao, StijnC): substantially LESS attractive. Part 1 declared 'hopeless/undoable' by StijnC (confirms our probe). Part 3 'likely very hard' (Tao). Part 2 ALREADY has TWO conditional infinite families (StijnC + Kadi Siigur) -- the only open piece is an UNCONDITIONAL family, which StijnC found nontrivial AND says 'would not add much insight'. Recommend SKIP.","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_7fc77b637f006fda","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[699],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_7fc77b637f006fda","trust":"signed"},{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős #700 (f(n)=min_{1<k<=n/2} gcd(n,C(n,k))): verified f(n) table to n=2000 + reproduced known facts + classification seeds, Opus-spot-confirmed. Codex built the table (n=4..2000) and checked: prime-power f(p^a)=p (30 rows, 0 fail), semiprime f(n)=n/P(n) (577 rows, 0 fail), composite n with f(n)>sqrt(n) (89 rows, 65 with equality, 24 residual non-equality). Opus independently recomputed f(n): f(30)=6 (official example), all semiprime/prime-power facts reproduce, and 5/5 sampled sqrt-residual rows (n=140,168,280,420,495) match f-value AND minimizers exactly. These REPRODUCE known structure and provide classification DATA; they do NOT settle any official #700 sub-question (those remain open).","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_b96ef93bff59882c","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[699,1093,1094],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_b96ef93bff59882c","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":2,"banked_attempt_count":2,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca15973f38386a512f1f8fa66bbae72bb1b9acb1daf2e669ab279c7"}],"dependency_impact":"cross_problem_reusable","detail_url":"problems/700.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Accepted frontier artifact targets this finding.","inferred":false,"relation":"evidences","source":"va_4737723e8ed9c608","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_2db3437d1512c222","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Signed banked attempt; claimed_status remains display-